Implemented Vercel Speed Insights for the Health AI project.

WHAT WAS IMPLEMENTED:
- Installed @vercel/speed-insights package (v2.0.0) using npm with --legacy-peer-deps flag to resolve peer dependency conflicts
- Added SpeedInsights component to the React application following Create React App best practices
- Integrated the component into the main App component for tracking across all routes

FILES MODIFIED:
- frontend/src/App.js - Added import for SpeedInsights component from @vercel/speed-insights/react and rendered it inside the Router component
- frontend/package.json - Added @vercel/speed-insights as a dependency
- frontend/package-lock.json - Updated with new dependency and its transitive dependencies

IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS:
Following the official Vercel Speed Insights documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart), I:

1. Installed the @vercel/speed-insights package using npm with --legacy-peer-deps flag due to TypeScript version conflicts between the existing react-scripts setup and optional peer dependencies from @vercel/speed-insights

2. Imported the SpeedInsights component from '@vercel/speed-insights/react' (the Create React App specific import path)

3. Added the <SpeedInsights /> component inside the Router component in the App function, which ensures it tracks performance metrics across all routes while maintaining the existing app structure

4. Verified the implementation by running a production build, which completed successfully with no errors

The SpeedInsights component will automatically:
- Track Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS, etc.)
- Send performance data to Vercel's Speed Insights dashboard
- Work seamlessly with the React Router setup

NOTES:
- The Speed Insights feature needs to be enabled in the Vercel dashboard for the project to start receiving data
- No additional configuration is required - the component works out of the box
- The implementation follows React best practices by placing the component at the root level to track the entire application
- Build artifacts were not included in the commit, only source files and package configuration
